<node id="Interest Rates">
  <data key="d0">Interest Rates</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Interest Rates refer to the cost of borrowing money, typically expressed as a percentage. Rising interest rates are a significant concern for investors, leading to declines and sell-offs in various markets, particularly in technology stocks. These rising rates act as a contributing factor to broader market selloffs, exacerbating investor concerns and impacting investment decisions across different sectors. The increase in interest rates can cause volatility in the financial markets, affecting stock prices and overall economic sentiment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-daa296a353c26f41dfc613743d24e936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-76068a2f95fd89e7ceb4741d4eb478ce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b8ec2739edb4ee1ccc4cf68534e90be5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2a0171ee9d19cc664d4d041d3e73ba2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07959bdb8bab221c9c80a1c3e85776b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cdd29ae3537f38a27c3848632ad51359&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c41e50d3a458388dc7fe53ece68ee69f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0944d4a59fb7a84bd79d2fca8361e518</data>
