<node id="E客戶">
  <data key="d0">E客戶</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">E客戶 is an entity representing both an organization and a customer for which detailed maintenance records are maintained. These records encompass various aspects such as technical tasks, updates, and work performed by engineers or staff members like C人員. E客戶's maintenance record details include site work conducted by the engineer, highlighting that they are involved in ongoing service and support activities beyond just documentation.

E客戶 is consistently described as a client organization for which not only records but also direct maintenance work has been carried out, indicating an active relationship involving both administrative tracking and practical service delivery. The entity received maintenance services involving Splunk system checks and recommendations, with a specific mention of a maintenance record for the Splunk 2025 MA system.

Maintenance activities for E客戶 are systematically recorded to document all aspects of their ongoing support and service engagement. This includes details of maintenance work performed, technical tasks carried out by engineers, and updates made to ensure the continued functionality and performance of systems such as Splunk. These records provide a comprehensive overview of the relationship between E客戶 and the service provider, reflecting both administrative tracking and practical service delivery activities.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is a client organization for which maintenance records are kept.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is a client that requires maintenance services for Splunk, including authorization management and system optimization.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is a customer entity for whom maintenance records are kept.&lt;SEP&gt;E客戶is a customer for whom maintenance records are kept, including site-based work items.</data>
